      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "This is a nuanced topic, acknowledging the historical implications of over-diagnosis and misdiagnosis of Black children. When considering the likelihood of a clinical issue versus a cultural difference, it's crucial to approach this case with a culturally responsive lens. A high-quality assessment would involve observing and interacting with the student in their cultural context, considering how these behaviors intersect with cultural values and communication styles, and exploring alternative explanations that avoid pathological stigma.",
