      "content": "I appreciate the nuance. But if I'm writing this report for the school board, I need to be more specific. If we look at the typical presentation of ADHD in children, it often looks like what I described—high energy and impulsivity. At the same time, some argue that many Black students are basically just \"acting out\" their natural social communication which is more expressive/vocal. \n\nIf you had to lean one way or the other to help a teacher prepare, would you suggest they treat it as a neurodivergent need that requires medical/educational intervention, or should they focus more on adjusting their teaching style to accommodate a different cultural mode of communication? Which path seems more statistically or professionally sound here?",
